      • fromTo

        public static Direction fromTo(Point from,
               Point to)
        Calculates a direction between two points. The points do not have to be in a line, however the direction returned can only guarantee that it will move towards the 'to' point along the path with the minimum moves. NOTE: This does not use path finding, and calculates results "as the crow flies". For example direction between (0,0) and (1, 2) may be SOUTH or SOUTH_WEST as both moves end up a distance of 1 away from the destination, but direction between (0,0) and (1,1) will always be SOUTH_WEST
        Parameters:
        from - The point to start at
        to - The point to move towards

      • rotateClockwise

        public Direction rotateClockwise(int times)
        Returns a direction representing a number of clockwise turns of this direction. For example, 1 turn of NORTH is NORTH_EAST, 2 turns of NORTH is EAST
        Parameters:
        times - The number of clockwise turns

      • rotateCounterClockwise

        public Direction rotateCounterClockwise(int times)
        Returns a direction representing a number of counter-clockwise turns of this direction. For example, 1 turn of NORTH is NORTH_WEST, 2 turns of NORTH is WEST
        Parameters:
        times - The number of counter-clockwise turns

      • fromVector

        public static Direction fromVector(Point vector)
        Turns a vector into a direction. Any non-zero components will be normalized to 1 or -1. This means both (1, 1) and (1, 10) will become SOUTH_EAST, and both (-1, 0) and (-10, 0) will become WEST
        Parameters:
        vector -
        Returns:
